SIMPLE: enumeration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enumeration
<hw>E*nu`mer*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enumeratio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧num⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
enumerating, making separate mention, or recounting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A detailed account, in which each thing is specially
noticed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Because almost every man we meet possesses these, we leave them
out of our <qex>enumeration</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A recapitulation, in the
peroration, of the heads of an argument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enumerative</ent>⟦br⟧
